parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the intake manifold can cause sudden and catastrophic damage, leading to engine compartment fires, damage to surrounding components, and potentially life-threatening situations.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A crack in the plastic fuel rail can cause fuel to collect in the intake manifold, leading to a potential explosion or fire.
The design flaw can cause engine damage, noise, and potentially lead to engine failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Radiator Failure and Coolant/Transmission Fluid Mixing
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the radiator can cause coolant and transmission fluid to mix, leading to transmission failure and potentially causing accidents.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the ABS system can cause extended stopping distance, skidding, and loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents or near-misses, and potentially resulting in injuries or fatalities.
